Given sequence $148,146,144, \ldots$ and average is 125.
$$
\begin{aligned}
\therefore \quad S_n &amp; =\frac{n}{2}[2 \times 148+(n-1)(-2)] \quad[\because d=-2] \\
&amp; =\frac{n}{2}[296-2 n+2] \\
&amp; =n[148-n+1]=n[149-n]
\end{aligned}
$$
Hence, $\quad 125=\frac{n[149-n]}{n}$
$$
\begin{aligned}
&amp; \Rightarrow \quad 125=149-n \\
&amp; \therefore \quad n=149-125=24 \\
